# GitHub sync

When you finish edits in this repo (`calendar-auto-add`):

1. `git status` — stage only intentional files (never commit `data/`, `.env`, or secrets).
2. `git add` the changed paths, then `git commit -m "…"` with a **one-line subject** plus optional 2–4 lines explaining what changed.
3. `git push origin main` (remote is `origin`).

Do this **before** ending the turn whenever you made substantive file changes, unless the user explicitly asked not to push.
